You will see people do this a lot, calling people confirmed, even without hard evidence. It basically means that they have reasonable evidence towards a person not being mafia, calling them confirmed is obviously an overdramatization on their part. What is actually meant is that there is, at the current moment, no need to look into these people, and that, for the moment, thinking of them as confirmed town is more beneficial than second guessing their opinions. Of course, nobody is ever truly confirmed, unless a cop has a clear and there is nothing to prevent that, or other such situations. It's more of a metaphorical as well as a game-plan strategical "confirmed" than anything.

Lunexia on Osu! 04/28/2023 3:50 PM
Often people talk of "purity" of reads. A "pure" read is one that is known, or thought of, as one coming from a town member. This means, that you can completely cross out any underlying intentions, such as covering for a mafia buddy, for example, or intentionally drawing attention somewhere in order to deceive. Therefor a pure read can be taken at face level, which is very helpful if you want to actually investigate into a read, because with pure reads you can be much more certain that the results actually mean something.

Often people talk of "purity" of reads. A "pure" read is one that is known, or thought of, as one coming from a town member. This means, that you can completely cross out any underlying intentions, such as covering for a mafia buddy, for example, or intentionally drawing attention somewhere in order to deceive. Therefor a pure read can be taken at face level, which is very helpful if you want to actually investigate into a read, because with pure reads you can be much more certain that the results actually mean something.
